@startuml
' V5 — Ceremonial disclosure via managed session (T3 example: Proxmox).
' Ceremony = explicit request + fresh presence proof + logged event;
' hygiene = decryption after proof, short-lived plaintext, permitted path
' (ADR-0018/0021).
!include style.iuml

actor "SOHO admin" as U
participant "Engine\n(ceremony service)" as E
participant "YubiKey" as Y
participant "Rotation profile\n(browser)" as P
participant "Proxmox web UI" as T

U -> E : open proxmox (launch request)
E -> U : request presence
U -> Y : touch
Y --> E : decrypt envelope entry (PIV)
E -> P : launch profile, navigate to target
E -> P : inject username + password\n(CDP recipe, no LLM)
opt TOTP second factor
  E -> P : inject code (engine-held seed,\noperational custody only)
  note over U, P
    or the user types the code
    from their own authenticator
  end note
end
P -> T : submit login
T --> P : authenticated session
E -> E : zeroize plaintext;\nemit disclosure event (presence)
E --> U : hand over authenticated window

note over P
  saving + sync hard-disabled;
  session cookie stays isolated
end note
@enduml
